Title: Object: Tomb of the Virgin Mary
Series: Views in Egypt, Palestine and other parts of the Ottoman Empire
Description: Plate 10 in volume II: prayers and pilgrims in a corridor with a gothic-arched roof: some in front of a niche behind a pillar in the right foreground, others in front of an altar at the end of the corridor in the left background; after Mayer; published state. 1803 Hand-coloured aquatint with etching
Bibliographic references: Abbey Travel / Travel in Aquatint and lithography 1770-1860 from the library of J.R.Abbey (369.II.10)
